Dataset Name: IMDB Movie Reviews

Description: This dataset consists of 50,000 movie reviews, evenly split into 25,000 reviews for training and 25,000 reviews for testing. The dataset is balanced, with each part containing an equal number of positive and negative reviews. It's primarily used for binary sentiment classification tasks.

Size: 80 MB

Number of Classes: 2 (Positive and Negative sentiment)

Number of Samples: 50,000 reviews

Data Type: Text (English).

Data Format: The data is presented in text files. Each review is a separate text file, and positive and negative reviews are stored in separate directories.

Preprocessing Requirements: Text preprocessing may be necessary depending on your use case, including removing HTML tags, converting to lowercase, removing punctuation and stopwords, tokenization, stemming/lemmatization, and converting the words to vectors.

Original Paper: "Learning Word Vectors for Sentiment Analysis"    (http://ai.stanford.edu/~amaas/data/sentiment/ )  by Andrew L. Maas, Raymond E. Daly, Peter T. Pham, Dan Huang, Andrew Y. Ng, and Christopher Potts 

Source Link Download: (https://keras.io/api/datasets/imdb/)
